RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 20500. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Two Races Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELMAR SUMMER chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the turn, dueled in upper stretch and edged clear late. LADYNESS raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the four path coming off the turn and gained ground in the stretch but could not get by the winner. PEEP'S DAY led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and in upper stretch and was caught late but kept on to the wire. LA PANDA raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the turn and flattened out in the lane. LUCKY FREEDOM trailed the field throughout, saved ground around the turn and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2 nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARGING AERO dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and in upper stretch, edged clear and held that margin to the wire. SHE'S REDNECKER bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, recovered to chase the leaders up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the bend, dueled in upper stretch and was outfinished late. LITTLE BIG dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle from the two path coming around the turn, was caught in upper stretch and kept on to the finish. ROYAL COURT trailed the field up the backstretch, began to move up while racing in the two and three path around the turn, and continued to gain ground mildly in the lane. PRINCESS LAKME raced off the pace on the outside early, navigated the turn from the two and three path and was empty in the stretch. DOC CARSON bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three and four path and made no bid.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Carol A. Reitman, Susan Gannon & Warren Miller

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 1. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLATOUTANDFOXY raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid while racing in the three and four path around the far turn, dueled in upper stretch and drew off while drifting in mildly in the final furlong. MONIQUES DAREDEVIL raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path headed into the far turn, dueled in upper stretch, gave way and kept on to the wire. BEAUTIFUL TIZ trailed the field on the inside through the opening half mile, raced in the three path around the far turn and passed tiring horses in the stretch. MA MEATLOAF led the field while saving ground around the firs turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second bend and tired in the lane. LUCKY LIZZIE saved ground around the first turn, chased the pace setter between horses up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the far turn and faded in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Th an $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEMIGHTDANCESALSA raced in the two path around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, opened up while racing in the three path around the far bend and held that margin to the wire. NURSE JUDY WHITNEY raced in the two path through the opening quarter of a mile, stalked the leader between horses up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and kept on to the wire while drifting mildly in the final furlong. HURRY UP DEAR bumped with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground mildly in the lane. FROSTY SECRET trailed the field from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, moved up while racing in the three path around the far turn and flattened out in the stretch. BRIENNE OF TARTH stumbled and bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the far turn and was empty in the lane. BAD AND BEAUTIFUL raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back headed into the second bend, raced in the three path from there and tired further in the stretch.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Peter David Knoll & Carol S. Knoll

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELARY chased the leader up the backstretch, raced in the four path around the turn, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and pulled clear while drifting mildly late. LUCKY SUNDAY raced at the back of the pack through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the four path, swung wide to began a bid entering the stretch and gained ground late. PARTY DREAM trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and gained ground in late stretch. DA JOURNEYGIRL led the field up the backstretch, continued to the show the way while racing in the three path around the turn, was caught in midstretch and weakened late. HIGH DONNA raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, came around the bend in the four path and faded in the lane. SORTARIA raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. UNCAPTURED DREAMS raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the three path and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 19600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In A llowances) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: R FUNNY BIZNESS led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled coming around the second bend, kicked clear and entered the stretch in the four path and drew off to the wire. PRUDENT SONG raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid approaching the half mile, dueled from the two and three path around the far bend and was no match for the winner in the lane. SUMMER AT THE SPA raced in the four path early, trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, angled in and improved position while saving ground around the far turn and finished evenly. MISTY GALE raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the four path and never threatened. TAKE TO THE SKIES raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, dropped back to trail the field while saving ground around the second bend and tired further in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIRL PRO raced in the two path around the first turn, led the field on the outside up the backstretch, kicked clear while racing in the two and three path around the far turn and drew off in the lane, under wraps at the wire. FIRST FAITH saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second bend and could not go with the winner in the stretch and chased that rival home. SUWANNEE CHICK raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the four path and gained ground mildly in the lane. BLACK KARMA raced in the two path early, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, moved up while saving ground around the far turn and flattened out in the stretch. SKYWARD PRINCESS raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the three path and weakened in the lane. CITY SPEAKER saved ground through the opening quarter of a mile, raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the two path and faded from there. DON DIVA raced in the four path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and made no bid. LIGEIA stalked the frontrunner on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the second bend and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 16600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 1 Allowed 2 lbs. ; A Race At A Mile Or Over Since November 1 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 ( Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MS BOOMBASTIC raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, navigated the far turn from the two path, launched a bid nearing the quarter pole and pulled clear late. THEUNCAPTUREDLADY saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid from the rail coming around the second bend, was caught in midstretch and kept on to the wire. J'S STAR JET led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled around the far turn while still in the two path and gave way in the final furlong. DONNA LIRICA raced in the two path early, tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and weakened in the lane. R D BLESSING saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the far bend, swung wide entering the stretch and had no kick. KISSES FOR HANNAH raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and tired from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 16600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 1 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race At A Mile Or Over Since November 1 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Race s Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CINDY'S SONG saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path coming around the second bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and held that margin to the wire. WATER WITCH veered out leaving the gate, raced in the four path early, trailed well behind the field up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path racing around the far turn and gained ground to the wire. DOROTHY'S THE BOSS saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and gained ground while drifting mildly late. BALI MOON chased the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the second turn from the four path and finished evenly. BARBARA dueled from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the second bend and tired in the lane. GLITTER BAY raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, angled in to save ground around the far turn and was empty in the stretch.
